subSubSection.paragraph:
Male terminalia
(
Figs. 38–44
): Black. Medioapical region of hypandrium with concavity (
Fig. 39
). Epandrium wide basally with finger-like lobe placed dorsally. Apex of finger-like lobe rounded in lateral view (
Fig. 40
); subepandrial sclerite without lateral projections, apical margin rounded (
Fig. 41
); gonocoxite with apical 1/3 digitiform (
Fig. 42
); gonostyle subrectangular, covered with small setae anteriorly and with long setae posteriorly (
Figs. 42, 43
); aedeagus with two long prongs (
Fig. 44
); ejaculatory apodeme wide in lateral view (
Fig. 44
). 
Female terminalia
(
Fig. 46, 47
): Tergite VIII expanded laterally (
Figs. 46, 47
); tergite IX+X slightly membranous medially (
Fig. 46
); apex of sternite VIII truncate with mediaoapical slit (
Fig. 47
); hypoproct with spiniform setae; median sclerite at posterior end of furca (remnant of tergite IX) absent; two oval sclerotized spermathecal capsules.

